[2026-03-12T17:54:20Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017XMRKDuxAWjGZBtTmPAAFU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary: RunStore error_message Handling\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase and found all code related to RunStore's handling of error_message. Here's the complete picture:\n\n### 1. Domain Type Definition\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 31-47)**\n- `Run` struct includes `ErrorMessage string` field (line 40)\n- Method `Fail(msg string)` (lines 108-112) sets the ErrorMessage and marks run as failed\n- The field is populated when a run fails and persisted through the store\n\n### 2. RunStore Port/Interface Definition\n**File: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 10-19)**\n- `RunStore` interface defines: `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, etc.\n- No explicit error_message-specific methods; handled generically through the Run domain type\n- The interface operates on complete `*domain.Run` objects\n\n### 3. SQLite Adapter Implementation\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`**\n\n**Database Schema (lines 46-88):**\n- Line 78: `ALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN error_message TEXT` (idempotent migration)\n- ErrorMessage is nullable TEXT column in the `runs` table\n\n**Creating Runs (lines 133-141):**\n- `CreateRun()` inserts error_message as parameter 8 in the INSERT statement (line 135)\n\n**Reading Runs (lines 143-161):**\n- `runSelectCols` constant (line 144) includes `COALESCE(error_message,'')` to handle NULL values\n- `scanRun()` function (lines 147-161) reads error_message from database row\n- Error_message is populated in the Run struct at line 151\n\n**Updating Runs (lines 174-182):**\n- `UpdateRun()` updates error_message as parameter 5 in UPDATE statement (line 176)\n\n**Listing Operations:**\n- `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`, `ListChildRuns()` all use the standard `runSelectCols` constant and `scanRuns()` helper, preserving error_message\n- `ListRunsSince()` (lines 394-415) also includes error_message via `runSelectCols`\n\n**Special: FailStaleRuns (lines 418-429):**\n- When daemon restarts, marks pending/running runs as failed\n- Sets error_message to `\"daemon restarted while run was active\"` (line 421)\n- This is the only hardcoded error message in the store\n\n### 4. gRPC Server Usage\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`**\n\n**Creating Errors (lines 147, 167, 344):**\n- Failures during image ensure, container start, or container exit call `run.Fail()` with descriptive error message\n- UpdateRun persists the error_message to database\n\n**Returning in ListRuns (line 409):**\n- Maps `run.ErrorMessage` to `pb.RunSummary.ErrorMessage` in the response\n\n**Returning in GetStatus (line 430):**\n- Maps `run.ErrorMessage` to `pb.GetStatusResponse.ErrorMessage` in the response\n\n**Returning in StreamLogs (lines 515, 573, 625):**\n- Sends ErrorMessage in LogEntry message when run completes (non-running state)\n\n### 5. Host Workflow Runner\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` (lines 134)**\n- When host workflow execution fails with error, calls `hostRun.Fail(runErr.Error())` (line 134)\n- Persists error message via UpdateRun before returning result\n\n### 6. Web Handler\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (line 96)**\n- In tests, sets `run.ErrorMessage` when creating failed runs for testing\n\n### 7. Protobuf API Definitions\n**File: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`**\n- `GetStatusResponse` message (line 43): includes `error_message` field\n- `RunSummary` message (line 104): includes `error_message` field\n\n### 8. Comprehensive Tests\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`**\n\n**TestRunErrorMessage (lines 319-344):**\n- Creates run with error message via `run.Fail()`\n- Verifies persistence and retrieval via GetRun\n- Tests update preservation of error_message\n\n**TestRunErrorMessageInList (lines 346-361):**\n- Verifies error_message appears in ListRuns results\n\n**TestStore_FailStaleRuns (lines 590-630):**\n- Tests the daemon restart scenario where stale runs are marked failed\n- Verifies the standard error message is set (line 618, 624)\n\n**Domain Tests:**\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go` (lines 54-61)**\n- TestRun_Fail() verifies the Fail() method sets ErrorMessage and state correctly\n\n### Key Data Flow Summary\n\n1. **Writing:** `run.Fail(message)` → sets `ErrorMessage` and `State=Failed` → `CreateRun()` or `UpdateRun()` → SQLite persists to `runs.error_message` column\n2. **Reading:** SQL query with `COALESCE(error_message,'')` → `scanRun()` → populates `Run.ErrorMessage` struct field\n3. **API Exposure:** `Run.ErrorMessage` → mapped to gRPC `RunSummary.error_message` or `GetStatusResponse.error_message` in responses\n4. **Special Case:** Daemon restart calls `FailStaleRuns()` which updates pending/running runs with standard error message\n\nAll file paths provided are absolute paths within the `/workspace` directory."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3ae3483ee3d6e395 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61140\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 28169</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9809350-ad4b-4126-9f85-6f6c371f5603","uuid":"d824f753-b9a0-455a-9401-4445a2d7b3fd","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all code related to the RunStore's handling of error_message. I need to understand:\n1. Where error_message is written/stored (look in adapters, particularly sqlite)\n2. The RunStore port/interface definition\n3. The domain types for Run that include error_message\n4. Any existing tests for RunStore\n\nSearch thoroughly across internal/adapters, internal/ports, internal/domain, and any other relevant directories.","agentId":"a3ae3483ee3d6e395","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfec